body: Looks like everything runs on CPU. You need CUDA for this build along with TensorRT, I think.

This is running on CUDA and a V100. I can confirm by nvidia-smi. TensorRT doesnt increase the speed, but I have a reproducible issue for that here: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/7230

Hi @oborchers, I think this is due to CUDA kernel missing for Pad and LessOrEqual ops. The other "Force fallback to CPU execution for node" are expected, since they are doing shape-related computation. 

Could you please check your Pad node's input type? I guess guess they are of "int" types?

@SherlockNoMad: Ok, thank you for the fast reply! I have uploaded all 10,609 messages here:
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oborchers/Medium_Repo/master/Putting%20GPT-Neo%20into%20Production%20using%C2%A0ONNX/GPT-Neo_Failures.txt

Most of them look as follows:
```
CUDA kernel not found in registries for Op type: Pad node name: Pad_4368
CUDA kernel not found in registries for Op type: Pad node name: Pad_3801
CUDA kernel not found in registries for Op type: LessOrEqual node name: LessOrEqual_7094
Force fallback to CPU execution for node: Gather_5
Force fallback to CPU execution for node: Unsqueeze_17
Force fallback to CPU execution for node: Slice_37
Force fallback to CPU execution for node: Squeeze_38
Force fallback to CPU execution for node: Div_66
Force fallback to CPU execution for node: Add_35901
```

I will further check the pad node type and report back

LessOrEqual CUDA kernel is recently merged into master. 
We might be still missing the CUDA kernel for Pad with int inputs types.
Thank you! I will try to check the other ops next week, as we shifted priorities.

any update on this? I'm also getting the similar error. 

Running on similar setup

@mjay2016 : Not from my side, but its likely we are soon going to need this functionality as well. @SherlockNoMad : Do you have an update on the issue?

@oborchers This has been fixed in the latest version of onnxruntime i.e. 1.8.

With no build I no longer see the following message.

"CUDA kernel not found in registries for Op type: Pad node name: Pad_4368" 

Regards,
MJay
@mjay2016 : Thank you. Do you see any significant speedups compared to base torch?
@tianleiwu - Do you know if can/should run this model with any offline transformer model optimization tools prior to running with ORT for best performance ?

Hi @oborchers,

Can you try to build from source (master) and try again ? 

Subsequent to this, we have fixed an issue with registration of `Pad` kernels for the CUDA EP and improved the kernel's performance. Based on the logs you shared above, I think the 6 Pad nodes should be placed on CUDA now and its perf should be better than before. So the improvement should be two-fold which I think should go a long way to closing the 2x gap with Torch.
